# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback.
# Any path that is not a real static asset is served index.html (HTTP 200)
# so React Router can resolve client-side routes on hard-refresh, deep links,
# and email/OAuth callback URLs. Static files in /assets/* are matched first
# and served directly, so this rule never shadows real bundles.
# A MISSING hashed chunk must return a REAL 404 — never fall through to the SPA
# index.html (200, text/html). During a deploy's propagation window an edge that
# does not yet have /assets/<hash>.js otherwise answers that URL with the SPA
# fallback; the browser then caches text/html under the IMMUTABLE asset URL, so
# dynamic import() keeps failing and the app white-screens permanently — even
# after Ctrl+Shift+R (a plain reload cannot evict an immutable-cached entry).
# A real 404 is never cached as the asset and lets lazyWithRetry / the boot
# recovery reload cleanly. Existing chunks are matched as static files first, so
# this only ever affects a chunk that truly is not on this deployment.
# (2026-07-06 poisoned-cache incident.)
/assets/*    /404.html    404
/*    /index.html   200
